# StudioFlow Color System & UI Guidelines

This document defines the official color palette and UI guidelines for the StudioFlow application. All new features and UI components should follow these rules consistently.

## Phase Colors (Workflow Stages)

The 5 workflow phases have specific brand colors that should be used throughout the application:

| Phase | Color Name | Hex Code | Usage |
|-------|-----------|----------|-------|
| **Design Concept** | Purple | `#a657f0` | First workflow phase, design boards, concept work |
| **3D Rendering** | Orange | `#f6762e` | 3D visualization phase |
| **Client Approval** | Teal | `#14b8a6` | Client review and approval workflows |
| **Drawings** | Indigo | `#6366ea` | Technical drawings phase |
| **FFE** | Pink/Magenta | `#e94d97` | Furniture, fixtures, equipment phase |

## How to Use These Colors

### In Tailwind CSS
Use arbitrary value syntax for exact colors:
```tsx
// Background colors
className="bg-[#a657f0]"  // Design Concept purple
className="bg-[#f6762e]"  // 3D orange
className="bg-[#14b8a6]"  // Client Approval teal
className="bg-[#6366ea]"  // Drawings indigo
className="bg-[#e94d97]"  // FFE pink

// Text colors
className="text-[#a657f0]"

// Border colors
className="border-[#a657f0]"

// Ring colors
className="ring-[#a657f0]"
```

### Light/Muted Variants
For backgrounds and hover states, use opacity variants:
```tsx
className="bg-[#a657f0]/10"  // 10% opacity for light backgrounds
className="bg-[#a657f0]/20"  // 20% opacity for hover states
className="border-[#a657f0]/30"  // 30% opacity for subtle borders
```

### Import from Constants
Always import phase colors from the central constants file:
```tsx
import { PHASE_COLORS } from '@/constants/colors'

// Usage
<div style={{ backgroundColor: PHASE_COLORS.DESIGN_CONCEPT.primary }} />
// Or with Tailwind arbitrary values
<div className={`bg-[${PHASE_COLORS.DESIGN_CONCEPT.primary}]`} />
```

