## Icons - NO EMOJIS RULE

**CRITICAL: Use Lucide React icons ONLY. Never use emojis in the UI.**

### Why No Emojis?
- Emojis render differently across operating systems and browsers
- Lucide icons provide consistent, professional appearance
- Icons can be styled with colors, sizes, and animations
- Better accessibility support

### Icon Usage

Always import icons from `lucide-react`:

```tsx
import { 
  Palette,      // Design Concept phase
  Box,          // 3D Rendering phase
  Users,        // Client Approval phase
  Ruler,        // Drawings phase
  Sofa,         // FFE phase
  Check,        // Completed/Success
  Clock,        // Time/Pending
  AlertTriangle,// Warning
  X,            // Close/Error
  Plus,         // Add
  Settings,     // Settings
  FileText,     // Documents
  FolderOpen,   // Projects
  Home,         // Home/Dashboard
} from 'lucide-react'
```

### Phase Icons Mapping

| Phase | Icon | Import |
|-------|------|--------|
| Design Concept | Palette | `import { Palette } from 'lucide-react'` |
| 3D Rendering | Box | `import { Box } from 'lucide-react'` |
| Client Approval | Users | `import { Users } from 'lucide-react'` |
| Drawings | Ruler | `import { Ruler } from 'lucide-react'` |
| FFE | Sofa | `import { Sofa } from 'lucide-react'` |

### Icon Styling

```tsx
// Basic usage
<Palette className="w-5 h-5" />

// With brand color
<Palette className="w-5 h-5 text-[#a657f0]" />

// White on colored background
<div className="bg-[#a657f0] p-2 rounded-lg">
  <Palette className="w-5 h-5 text-white" />
</div>
```

